<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,613,1036]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,685,711]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Note</emphasis>
. This species was recognized among the “Yarkand spiders”, a collection lacking species or geographical labels, due to its size, “over 5 lines” (~ 
<quantity box="[601,708,721,748]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="10.5">10.5 mm</quantity>
), and pale coloration. In the description, O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pickard-Cambridge, O." pageId="17" pageNumber="73" refId="ref13520" refString="Pickard-Cambridge, O. (1885) Araneidea. In: Scientific results of the second Yarkand mission; based upon the collections and notes of the late Ferdinand Stoliczka. Ph. D. Government of India, Calcutta, 115 pp." type="book" year="1885">Pickard-Cambridge (1885)</bibRefCitation>
compared this species with 
<taxonomicName authority="Thorell, 1856" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1856" box="[542,827,757,784]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trochosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terricola">
<emphasis box="[542,668,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">T. terricola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thorell, T." box="[674,827,757,784]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" pagination="61 - 176" refId="ref14155" refString="Thorell, T. (1856) Recensio critica aranearum suecicarum quas descripserunt Clerckius, Linnaeus, de Geerus. Nova Acta Regiae Societatis Scientiarum Upsaliensis, Series 3, 2 (1), 61 - 176." type="journal article" year="1856">Thorell, 1856</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="De Geer" baseAuthorityYear="1778" box="[881,1001,757,783]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trochosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruricola">
<emphasis box="[881,1001,757,783]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">T. ruricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the generotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,613,1036]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,793,819]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Description</emphasis>
. See O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pickard-Cambridge, O." box="[431,735,793,820]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" refId="ref13520" refString="Pickard-Cambridge, O. (1885) Araneidea. In: Scientific results of the second Yarkand mission; based upon the collections and notes of the late Ferdinand Stoliczka. Ph. D. Government of India, Calcutta, 115 pp." type="book" year="1885">Pickard-Cambridge (1885)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<typeStatus box="[745,849,793,819]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Holotype</typeStatus>
faded. Measurements of the 
<typeStatus box="[1171,1269,793,819]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[1275,1298,794,820]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: total length 11.0; carapace 5.0 long, 4.0 wide; Leg I 11.7 (3.3, 1.9, 2.6, 2.3, 1.6).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,613,1036]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,865,891]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Comments</emphasis>
. The shape of the epigyne indicates that this species belongs to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mozaffarian &amp; Marusik" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[1086,1189,865,891]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trochosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1086,1189,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Trochosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, unlike other species placed by O. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pickard-Cambridge, O." box="[298,598,901,928]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" refId="ref13520" refString="Pickard-Cambridge, O. (1885) Araneidea. In: Scientific results of the second Yarkand mission; based upon the collections and notes of the late Ferdinand Stoliczka. Ph. D. Government of India, Calcutta, 115 pp." type="book" year="1885">Pickard-Cambridge (1885)</bibRefCitation>
in this genus. The relationship of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1885" box="[975,1102,901,927]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trochosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adjacens">
<emphasis box="[975,1102,901,927]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">T. adjacens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with other congeners remains unclear. Most, if not all, females in the genus 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mozaffarian &amp; Marusik" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[666,769,937,963]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Trochosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[666,769,937,963]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">Trochosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be distinguished from each other, especially singletons. To correctly classify this species, males are required from the 
<typeStatus box="[905,953,974,1000]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1313,1009,1036]" pageId="17" pageNumber="73" type="distribution">
